# Review Checklist

Use this checklist for pull requests that touch Pathogen UI, styles, previews, or design-system documentation.

## Intent And Contract

- [ ] Does every visual choice clarify workflow structure, state, hierarchy, or navigation?
- [ ] Does the change follow the [Design Contract](01-design-contract)?
- [ ] If it introduces an exception, is the rationale documented?
- [ ] Should any local pattern become a shared Pathogen component or token?
- [ ] Does the UI feel **inevitable** for the task — not decorated after the fact?

## Tokens And Colour

- [ ] Semantic roles (`--pvc-color-*`) used where available?
- [ ] No new raw `slate-*` utilities (use `neutral-*`)?
- [ ] Public `--color-primary-*` override contract preserved?
- [ ] Status colours used only for status meaning?
- [ ] No hard-coded host brand colours in shared components?
- [ ] Strong colour blocks limited to selection, focus, status, navigation, grouping?
- [ ] Any new solid-fill state (not just buttons) darkens on hover, matching the canonical rule?
- [ ] `success` / `warning` used only as base text/border/icon roles, not as a solid fill?

## Typography And Spacing

- [ ] Product rhythm stays on 14px / 16px unless hierarchy requires more?
- [ ] Labels use control scale + semibold where they identify settings/rows/controls?
- [ ] Spacing uses 4px-base scale (`gap-1` … `gap-8`) without arbitrary values?
- [ ] Page headings left to `Pathogen::Typography::Heading`?

## Radius And Surfaces

- [ ] Radius matches role: control (2–4px), action (6px), panel (8px)?
- [ ] No `rounded-xl`+ on standard product surfaces?
- [ ] Surfaces use border + background before shadow?
- [ ] Overlay shadow only on tooltips, popovers, menus?

## Buttons

- [ ] At most one `primary` + `solid` per action group?
- [ ] Secondary/dismissive actions use `neutral` + `outline` or `ghost`?
- [ ] `danger` + `solid` reserved for confirmed destructive steps?
- [ ] Icon-only buttons have distinct accessible names?
- [ ] Toolbar/grid actions use `small` without going below documented minimum targets, **and** keep at least 8px between adjacent `small` targets?
- [ ] Solid-fill hover states darken, never lighten?
- [ ] No solid-fill success/warning surfaces (unsupported until the token ladder lands — see [Tokens → Token Migration Roadmap](02-tokens))?

## Geometry And Layout

- [ ] Controls, labels, data, and actions align to a clear grid?
- [ ] Dividers and borders trace real structure?
- [ ] Asymmetry tied to workflow priority, not decoration?
- [ ] Any Bauhaus-derived shape, offset, or colour block encodes selection, focus, status, navigation, or workflow priority — not used as poster-style ornament? (See [Overview → Bauhaus](00-overview) for the conditional rule; this is not a blanket ban on geometric structure.)

## Focus And Accessibility

- [ ] Visible `focus-visible` treatment in light and dark mode?
- [ ] Prefer `--pvc-color-focus` for new/migrated focus rings?
- [ ] Focus ring stays visually distinct from `--pvc-color-accent` in **both** modes (not just light)?
- [ ] State not communicated by colour alone?
- [ ] Semantic HTML, WCAG AA contrast, screen-reader names?
- [ ] `prefers-reduced-motion` respected?
- [ ] Forced-colours / high-contrast checked on custom controls?

## Dark Mode

- [ ] Canvas avoids default large `neutral-950` shells?
- [ ] Borders, muted text, hover, selected, disabled, and focus still clear?
- [ ] Focus ring does not collapse onto the same value as accent (fixed `primary-500`, not a mode-flipped shade)?
- [ ] Dense grids use deeper inset only inside framed regions?
- [ ] Same radius and spacing logic as light mode?

## Previews

- [ ] Realistic clinical/lab/public-health workflow context?
- [ ] No marketing gradients, hero layouts, or heavy shadows?
- [ ] Same token language as shipped components?
- [ ] Checked in light **and** dark mode?

## Validation Commands

Run checks that match the touched surface:

| Change type | Command |
|-------------|---------|
| CSS / tokens / utilities | `pnpm run build:css:check` |
| Ruby components | `bin/test` |
| JavaScript interaction | `pnpm test` |
| Visible components | Lookbook review, light + dark |
